1 Overview
**********

The ‘wikipedia.el’ package provides a comprehensive Emacs interface for
Wikipedia.  It builds on top of ‘mediawiki.el’, which handles the
low-level protocol details, and adds higher-level workflows for editing,
reviewing, and managing Wikipedia content.

   The package requires Emacs 29.1 or later and ‘mediawiki.el’ for the
underlying API communication.  Optionally, ‘gptel’ provides AI-powered
features (citation generation, edit summary generation, and watchlist
review scoring), and ‘pangram.el’ provides AI-generated text detection.
When available, corresponding groups appear in the transient menu (*note
Transient menu::).  Before using any commands, you must configure at
least one wiki site via ‘mediawiki-site-alist’ and establish a session
with ‘wikipedia-login’ (*note Session management::).

   The package is organized around several core workflows:

   • *Page editing*: open pages for editing in ‘mediawiki-mode’ buffers,
     preview rendered HTML, and publish changes back to the wiki (*note
     Page editing::).

   • *Draft management*: save work-in-progress edits as local files that
     persist across sessions (*note Draft management::).

   • *Watchlist*: browse your watchlist with a grouped, expandable
     interface that shows recent changes organized by page, with unread
     tracking and background prefetching of diffs (*note Watchlist::).

   • *Revision history*: inspect the full revision history of any page,
     view diffs between arbitrary revisions, and navigate between
     historical snapshots (*note Revision history::).

   • *User inspection*: view user contributions, visit user pages, send
     thanks, and look up detailed editing statistics via XTools (*note
     User inspection::, *note XTools statistics::).

   • *Local mirror*: synchronize watched pages to a local SQLite
     database for offline browsing and faster access (*note
     Synchronization and local mirror::).

   • *Diff follow mode*: automatically display diffs as you navigate
     entries in the watchlist, history, or contributions buffers (*note
     Diff follow mode::).

   • *AI-powered editing* (requires ‘gptel’): generate Wikipedia
     citation templates, produce edit summaries from diffs, and score
     watchlist changes by review priority (*note AI commands::).

   • *Wiki link completion*: get title suggestions from the MediaWiki
     API as you type inside ‘[[...]]’ links (*note Wiki link
     completion::).

   All commands are accessible through a unified transient menu (*note
Transient menu::).

   The development repository is on GitHub
(https://github.com/benthamite/wikipedia).


